HEADWORD: Adulterous
<hw>A*dul"ter*ous</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Guilty of, or given to, adultery; pertaining to adultery;
illicit.</def> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Characterized by adulteration; spurious.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧An <xex>adulterous</xex> mixture.⟦rdquo⟧ <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Smollett.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Adulterously</ent>⟦br⟧
